		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Barbarian(well really general)warrior tips.</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Seravek</a> | 
		            7/2/2001 2:18:58 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">So you decided to play a warrior who will not get squished by a giant and one who can actually count to 10.  The barbarian is the closest thing I encountered to a knight which is good.  Anyway, a few tips for ya warrs. coming up in this world.  <BR>
#1.  Setting up your hot keys:  This is critical for getting your warr off on the right foot.  I have taunt and sense heading hotkeyed and they should definitely both be gray anytime you battle and use your sense heading when not battling too at early levels.  Also, set up hot keys of your inventory and have your dual wield or 2handed weapons in it.  This is great for switching out your weapons fast which is good when that mobs damage shield is ripping you apart cause your hacking with 2 weapons...time to whip out the 2hander..quick!  Lets see, your inc. message is an essential for your party to know company is coming/another is an evac. message so they know when to book/and a battle cry too is just fun to have and gloat!  Hehe.  Have an assist button cause yes sometimes you will be the secondary tank and YOU ALL NEED TO HIT THE SAME DAMN TARGET!  Finally, a location and corpse button are mandatory!  When your gonna die hit your loc button to get your location coordinates or you will have to search all over the place for it or beg a necro to find it which will cost you some dough.  The corpse command is awesome for summoning your corpse without having to target and grab your junk and while a mob beats you to death.  You will drag it to you and also another great trick when the mobs on your tail or its too hot in the area is to hit corpse to summon and then run while constantly hitting your button to drag it behind you.  Hehe....did it yesterday while a dragoon was on my tail...jumping and screeming helps too!  Anyway, thats some good hot key buttons for ya to set up and save time, get skills, and basically show that you are a professional warrior.<BR>
<BR>
#2Taunting:  The skill that warriors are valued for.  Taunting is a skill that always should be used in battle to keep those weak casters on you.  Many things affect your taunting effectivness like damage, quick damage, your taunt button of course, disarming, begging from a mob when not attacking, and just standing between the mob and what it wants to kill.  Use your taunt/disarm buttons in unison with always standing in front of the mob to keep it pissed...at higher levels its gonna take some low delay damage items to keep it off your nukers and healers so you might want to forego that wurmy after lv45 cause the delay wont keep that mob on ya after the wizzy drops the bomb.  When an enchanter is in your group and he mezzes make sure you place a few taunts on it before you attack your target cause one it breaks he gonna have an up close and personal chat with him.  Finally when that mob darts for your cler. or caster when he throws that spell I have found it very effective to jump over him and turn my body mid air to stick myself in between the caster and mob...that pisses him off and gets you in damag/taunting position quickly without having to run then turn yourself to face him...just a thought.<BR>
<BR>
#3.  Weapons skills and bind wound:As far as weapons go I regret to say that I stuck with slashing weapons the whole time.  If I could try again I would include piercing cause Kunark has some good ones out there.  Anyway, from newbie before dual wield use a 2hs!  Why?  Cause it maxes out way slower than your 1hs does when ya gets the dual wield.  Once that happens get you 2 langseaxes and watch that skill fly.  Also around level 13-24 an axe of the ironback will keep your 2hs competitive and maxed out along with your 1hs's....MAX out your skills for every level!  Bind wound is not gonna be a real factor unless you twinking then you can afford to pay 1plat 2gold(for my charisma!)for a stack.  Once you can afford it use it to heal some of your group members when they are resting, ppls hurt that you meet, and uh...yourself of course when you are hurt!  Try to work on it often cause it lessens your down time alot and in a hostile area can save your life and get you the hell out without having to walk out critically wounded.<BR>
<BR>
Well thats enough babbling, there is so much more to the warrior but then I would be writing a whole guide and I'm at work right now!  HEHE! Just know that you are the tank, you are the leader, and you will probably be the one who holds off the mobs (yell your evac button!)while the casters and others book it...and sometimes you will die.  Thats your life but use these skills and others you aquire and gain a reputation throughout the land.  For theres no better honor and feeling than saving someones life and having groups want you to join without even campaigning for one.  Until then, bring honor to the wolves of the north.<BR>
<BR>
Seravek Soulblightur<BR>
40 Meat Grinder
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
